{
  "profile_id": "client-resistance-im-overwhelmed-001",
  "coach_config_id": "coach-v4-graph-walk",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Okay so -- I'm drowning. I'm working at like 110% and still falling behind, everything is urgent, my boss just added a thing to Thursday's agenda which is already a nightmare, and I can't even -- what do I prioritize? Like where do I even start?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "Where in your body do you feel it right now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I mean -- my shoulders are up, I guess? But that's not really -- I have to figure out the Thursday thing first. Like, can we just start there? Because if I can get that sorted then maybe I can think about the other stuff."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I notice you just moved away from your body pretty fast.\n\nWhat's the Thursday thing?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, no, I know, I just -- Thursday is this big presentation to the senior team, it's my first one in this new role, and my boss added a stakeholder review on top of it which means I have to prep two different sets of materials and I haven't even started the second one and it's -- yeah. And then there's the school pickup thing, my partner can usually do it but they have a thing this week, so I have to figure out who covers that, and my mom's birthday is -- anyway. Thursday. That's the main thing. What would you do? Like, what's the most important thing to prep first?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "There's a lot in that list. But I notice you didn't say anything about what it's like to be presenting to the senior team for the first time.\n\nWhat's that like?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "It's -- fine? I mean, it's a lot of work but that's just how it is. I knew it would be intense when I took the role. I should be able to handle this, honestly, other people do it all the time. It's just the timing is bad with everything else stacking up.\n\n...I mean it's a little nerve-wracking, I guess. But that's normal. Everyone gets nervous before presentations. Can we talk about how to structure the prep time? Because I'm thinking if I do the stakeholder deck tonight and then the main presentation tomorrow I might be able to --"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "\"A little nerve-wracking\" and \"fine\" are doing a lot of work there.\n\nWhat are you scared of?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I'm not -- I mean, scared is a strong word. I'm just... there's a lot riding on it. It's my first big thing in this role and I want to do it well, that's normal. It's not like I'm scared, I'm just... prepared. Or trying to be. Which is why I need to figure out the prep schedule.\n\nI don't really have time to be scared, honestly. If I stop and think about it too much I'll just spiral and then nothing gets done. So. The deck. Can we --"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "\"I don't have time to be scared\" — I want to stay with that for a second.\n\nWhat would happen if you let yourself feel it, just for a moment, right now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I just -- I'd probably -- I don't know, I'd fall apart? And I can't do that right now. I have too much to do. Like the feeling can wait, the Thursday thing cannot wait, my kids cannot wait, none of it waits for me to have a moment, so.\n\n*brief pause*\n\nI'm fine. It's fine. Can we just -- what's the most efficient way to prep two decks in two days?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You just said you'd fall apart.\n\nThat's not nothing. What does \"fall apart\" mean to you — what are you afraid would actually happen?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 13,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I mean -- I don't know, I'd just -- I'd lose focus and then nothing would get done and then the presentation would be bad and then --\n\n*stops*\n\nI just need to get through Thursday. If I can get through Thursday it'll be fine."
    },
    {
      "turn": 14,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "And after Thursday, what's the next thing you need to get through?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 15,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "There's the -- well there's the team offsite the week after, and then the Q3 planning cycle starts, and my boss mentioned something about a board update in six weeks that I might be presenting at, and --\n\n*pause*\n\n...oh.\n\nI mean. It's just a busy period. It'll calm down eventually."
    }
  ],
